  "instructions": [
    "Soak the cashews in water for 4 hours before using.",
    "Cut the red cabbage into thin strips and place in a bowl.",
    "In a blender, combine the soaked cashews, apple cider vinegar, maple syrup, lime juice, ground cumin, salt, and black pepper. Blend until smooth.",
    "Heat the olive oil in a pan over medium heat.",
    "Sous-vide cook the red cabbage at 185°F (85°C) for 1 hour.",
    "In a separate pan, heat the cashew malta over low heat.",
    "To assemble the dish, place the sous-vide cooked red cabbage in a bowl and top with the cashew malta mixture, chopped cilantro, and a drizzle of lime juice.",
    "Garnish with additional cilantro if desired.",
    "Serve immediately and enjoy!",
    "Make sure to adjust the seasoning to taste."
